    "title": "Cottage pie jacket potato",
    "subtitle": "A crisp-skinned jacket potato loaded with cottage pie filling",
    "excerpt": "Cottage pie filling piled onto a jacket potato is a practical hybrid of two British comfort food staples. The rich minced beef filling goes where the mash would normally sit, making a more substantial and textured meal than either dish alone.",
    "sourceNotes": "British home cooking combination of two staples. Using cottage pie filling on a jacket potato is a practical British weeknight shortcut that combines the familiar flavours of both dishes. It avoids the mash-making step while delivering a filling and satisfying meal.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "The jacket potato bakes while the cottage pie filling simmers on the hob, so the timing works well. Put the potatoes in first, start the filling about 30 minutes later. The filling needs to be fairly thick: a loose, watery filling will flood the plate rather than sitting on the potato. Reduce it well before serving.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
